<% content_for :title, "What's New · BiblioRata" %>

<div class="ps-news" data-controller="whats-new"
     data-whats-new-mode-value="seen"
     data-whats-new-version-value="<%= @version %>">

  <%# floating ornaments behind the header %>
  <span class="float-orn o1">&#10038;</span>
  <span class="float-orn o2">&#10086;</span>
  <span class="float-orn o3">&#9835;</span>
  <span class="float-orn o4">&#10022;</span>
  <span class="float-orn o5">&#10070;</span>

  <header class="news-head">
    <div class="eyebrow">&#10038; Fresh from the scriptorium &#10038;</div>
    <h1>What&rsquo;s new in BiblioRata</h1>
    <p class="sub">Built for the pulpit, the projection desk, and every phone in the pews.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="news-grid">

    <%# 1 — Preach Queue %>
    <section class="news-card c-rubric" style="--d: 0s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-queue">
          <div class="mock-qtitle">&#9835; Preach Queue</div>
          <div class="mock-qitem q1"><span class="ic">&#167;</span> Romans 8:28</div>
          <div class="mock-qitem q2"><span class="ic">&#9835;</span> Amazing Grace <em>4 stanzas</em></div>
          <div class="mock-qitem q3"><span class="ic">&#10086;</span> Welcome &amp; announcements</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9835;</span> The Preach Queue</h2>
      <p>Line up the whole service before it starts &mdash; scriptures, songs, and thoughts, in order.
         During the sermon, one click puts each item on the big screen.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 2 — Songs & thoughts as slides %>
    <section class="news-card c-gold" style="--d: .12s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-screen mock-slide">
          <div class="slide-t">AMAZING GRACE</div>
          <div class="stanzas">
            <span class="stanzaA">Amazing grace, how sweet the sound,<br>that saved a wretch like me&hellip;</span>
            <span class="stanzaB">Through many dangers, toils and snares,<br>I have already come&hellip;</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9836;</span> Songs &amp; thoughts, projected</h2>
      <p>Type lyrics or a note, leave a blank line between stanzas, and each stanza becomes its own
         beautiful slide &mdash; on the projector <em>and</em> on every phone following live.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 3 — AI study assistant %>
    <section class="news-card c-sage" style="--d: .24s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-ask">
          <div class="mock-go"><span class="lbl">Go to</span><span class="typed">azusa street</span><span class="caret"></span></div>
          <div class="mock-answer">
            <div class="t">AZUSA STREET REVIVAL</div>
            <div class="s">A 1906 revival in Los Angeles led by William J. Seymour&hellip;</div>
            <div class="b">&#10697; Put this on the screen</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#10038;</span> Ask anything, mid-sermon</h2>
      <p>The preacher mentions the crusaders, Azusa Street, the walls of Jericho&hellip; type it in the
         Go box and the study assistant answers with a projectable card plus the Scriptures that go with it.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 4 — Phone remote %>
    <section class="news-card c-cobalt" style="--d: .36s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-phone">
          <div class="ph-head"><span class="dot"></span> Connected</div>
          <div class="ph-pad">
            <div class="ph-btn">&#8249;</div>
            <div class="ph-btn next">&#8250;<span class="tapring"></span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="ph-verse">verse <span class="nums"><span>16</span><span>17</span><span>18</span></span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9742;</span> Your phone is the clicker</h2>
      <p>Scan a secret QR and walk anywhere in the room &mdash; next, previous, even chasing a called
         reference, straight from your pocket.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 5 — Stage display %>
    <section class="news-card c-ink" style="--d: .48s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-stage">
          <div class="st-head"><span>JOHN 3</span><span class="clock">10<i>:</i>42</span></div>
          <div class="st-now"><span class="l">now &middot; v16</span>For God so loved the world&hellip;</div>
          <div class="st-next"><span class="l">next &middot; v17</span>For God sent not his Son to condemn&hellip;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#8983;</span> The stage display</h2>
      <p>A confidence monitor for the pulpit: the current verse small, the <strong>next verse big</strong>,
         and a clock &mdash; the preacher always knows what&rsquo;s coming.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 6 — Screen themes %>
    <section class="news-card c-rose" style="--d: .6s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-screen mock-themes">
          <span class="th-verse">For God so loved the world</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#10022;</span> Dress the projection</h2>
      <p>Vellum, deep ink, or clean paper &mdash; pick the projector&rsquo;s look and text size from the
         console. It remembers your choice for next Sunday.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 7 — ⟲ Back %>
    <section class="news-card c-plum" style="--d: .72s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-back">
          <div class="bk-screen bk-a"><span class="t">JOHN 3:16</span><span class="x">For God so loved the world&hellip;</span></div>
          <div class="bk-screen bk-b"><span class="t">MILKY WAY GALAXY</span><span class="x">Our home galaxy, some 100,000 light-years across&hellip;</span></div>
          <div class="bk-key">&#10558;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#10558;</span> One press back</h2>
      <p>The preacher detours to an aid, then says <em>&ldquo;back to our text&rdquo;</em> &mdash; press
         <strong>Back</strong> (or <kbd>B</kbd>) and you&rsquo;re on the exact verse you left, instantly.
         It&rsquo;s on the phone remote too.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 8 — Pictures in the queue %>
    <section class="news-card c-teal" style="--d: .84s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-screen mock-pic">
          <div class="pic-frame">
            <span class="sun"></span>
            <span class="hill h1"></span>
            <span class="hill h2"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="pic-cap">HARVEST SUNDAY &middot; 10AM</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9670;</span> Pictures on the screen</h2>
      <p>Drop announcement slides and sermon graphics straight into the queue &mdash; one click projects
         them full-screen, and the congregation&rsquo;s phones see them too.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 9 — Go Live recap %>
    <section class="news-card c-ochre" style="--d: .96s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-live">
          <div class="lv-head"><span class="dot"></span> Following live <span class="chip"><span class="nums"><span>23</span><span>24</span><span>25</span></span> following</span></div>
          <div class="lv-lines">
            <span class="ln"></span><span class="ln"></span><span class="ln"></span><span class="ln"></span>
            <span class="hl"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9737;</span> Go Live &mdash; now with a takeaway</h2>
      <p>The congregation follows on their phones, verse by verse. And when the service ends, every
         phone receives <em>tonight&rsquo;s scriptures</em> &mdash; the full list, ready to keep reading at home.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 10 — Blank / holding screen %>
    <section class="news-card c-ink" style="--d: 1.08s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-screen mock-blank">
          <span class="orn">&#10022;</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9634;</span> Blank the screen in a tap</h2>
      <p>Before the service and between segments, snap the projector to a calm holding screen &mdash;
         one press of <strong>Blank</strong> (or the <kbd>.</kbd> key). Cue the next verse underneath;
         tap again and it&rsquo;s right there.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 11 — Song library %>
    <section class="news-card c-gold" style="--d: 1.2s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-library">
          <div class="lib-row"><span class="t">Amazing Grace</span><span class="tag hymn">hymnal</span></div>
          <div class="lib-row"><span class="t">Holy, Holy, Holy</span><span class="tag hymn">hymnal</span></div>
          <div class="lib-row pick"><span class="t">Our Anthem</span><span class="tag">yours</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9835;</span> Songs you don&rsquo;t retype</h2>
      <p>Pick a hymn from the built-in public-domain hymnal, or reuse any song you&rsquo;ve queued
         before &mdash; one tap fills the lyrics in. Build the music half of the service in seconds.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 12 — Reconnect / refresh reliability %>
    <section class="news-card c-cobalt" style="--d: 1.32s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-phone mock-rejoin">
          <div class="ph-head"><span class="dot"></span> <span class="rj-status">Reconnecting&hellip;</span></div>
          <div class="rj-lines">
            <span class="ln"></span><span class="ln"></span>
            <span class="hl"></span>
            <span class="ln"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9851;</span> It survives a hiccup</h2>
      <p>If a phone drops Wi-Fi mid-service, it snaps right back to the live verse the moment it
         reconnects &mdash; no stale screen. And if the projection window gets closed or refreshed,
         reopening it restores exactly what was up: passage, theme, even a blanked screen.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 13 — Reference on screen (the reference rides along as the verse advances) %>
    <section class="news-card c-rubric" style="--d: 1.44s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-screen mock-ref">
          <div class="ref-banner">JOHN&nbsp;3:<span class="nums"><span>16</span><span>17</span><span>18</span></span>
            &middot; KJV</div>
          <div class="ref-vnum nums"><span>16</span><span>17</span><span>18</span></div>
          <div class="ref-lines">
            <span>For God so loved the world&hellip;</span>
            <span>that he gave his only begotten Son&hellip;</span>
            <span>that whosoever believeth in him&hellip;</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#167;</span> The passage, named on screen</h2>
      <p>The congregation no longer sees a lonely &ldquo;16&rdquo; &mdash; the full reference rides across
         the top of every projected verse, like <em>John 3:16 &middot; KJV</em>, and follows along as you
         move, so anyone glancing up knows exactly where you are.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 14 — Emphasise a word: a tap, then it glows here AND on the phone beside it %>
    <section class="news-card c-gold" style="--d: 1.56s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-emph-pair">
          <div class="mock-screen mock-emph">
            <p>&hellip;the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy,
              <span class="glow">peace<span class="tapring"></span></span>, longsuffering&hellip;</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mock-emph-phone">
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span class="ln"></span><span class="ln"></span>
            <span class="word">peace</span>
            <span class="ln"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#10038;</span> Make the key word glow</h2>
      <p>When the minister leans on a word &mdash; <em>peace</em>, <em>grace</em>, <em>abide</em> &mdash; tap
         it on the verse and it lights up on the projector <em>and</em> on every following phone. Tap
         again to let it go.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 15 — Teaching anchor: wander to cross-refs, press H, snap home %>
    <section class="news-card c-plum" style="--d: 1.68s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-anchor">
          <div class="home">&#9875;&nbsp; JOHN 3:12 <span class="ping"></span></div>
          <div class="trail">
            <span class="d1">&#8594; Rom 5</span>
            <span class="d2">&#8594; Gen 1</span>
            <span class="key">press <b>H</b></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9875;</span> One key back to your text</h2>
      <p>Anchor your main teaching passage, wander off to as many cross-references as the sermon takes
         &mdash; then press <kbd>H</kbd> (or <kbd>&#8962;</kbd>) and you&rsquo;re back on the exact verse
         you paused at. No more hunting.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 16 — Queue several at once: type a comma list, three items drop in together %>
    <section class="news-card c-teal" style="--d: 1.8s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-batch">
          <div class="batch-type">
            <span class="lbl">Queue</span>
            <span class="typed">John 3:16, Rom 8:28, Ps 23</span>
            <span class="caret"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="batch-items">
            <div class="bi"><span class="ic">&#167;</span> John 3:16</div>
            <div class="bi"><span class="ic">&#167;</span> Romans 8:28</div>
            <div class="bi"><span class="ic">&#167;</span> Psalm 23</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9835;</span> Queue a stack in one go</h2>
      <p>For a fast-moving minister, type several references separated by commas
         (<em>John 3:16, Rom 8:28, Ps 23</em>) and they drop into the queue as separate items in a
         single tap &mdash; no more adding them one at a time.</p>
    </section>

    <%# 17 — Split projection: different scriptures side-by-side on the big screen %>
    <section class="news-card c-cobalt" style="--d: 1.92s">
      <div class="mock">
        <div class="mock-split">
          <div class="sp-region a">
            <div class="sp-ref">ROMANS&nbsp;8:28</div>
            <div class="sp-text">And we know that all things work together for good&hellip;</div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-region b">
            <div class="sp-ref">JEREMIAH&nbsp;29:11</div>
            <div class="sp-text">For I know the thoughts that I think toward you&hellip;</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2><span class="orn">&#9707;</span> Split the screen, two passages at once</h2>
      <p>Put up to four <em>different</em> scriptures side-by-side on the projector &mdash; a promise
         beside its fulfilment, the Law beside the Gospel. Click a side (or press <kbd>1</kbd>&ndash;<kbd>4</kbd>)
         to make it active, then <strong>Next</strong> or <strong>Go</strong> moves just that passage
         while the others hold steady.</p>
    </section>

  </div>

  <footer class="news-foot">
    <div class="rule-orn"><span class="line"></span><span>&#10086;</span><span class="line"></span></div>
    <%= link_to "Open a study and try it &rarr;".html_safe, root_path, class: "cta" %>
    <%= link_to "Read the field guide", guide_path, class: "cta secondary" %>
  </footer>
</div>
